Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Block
    This class creates the individual blocks for the game
    Coin
    This class is for the properties of a coin which is a token.
    Data
    Class is used for serialisation of the game in case a game is not completed.
    DestroyBlocks
    A type of token that is used to remove/destroy all the blocks on the screen.
    Game
    Game contains the scene for the actual game and handles all the interaction between all GUI components
    GameOver
    Screen when the player loses the the game, ie, the length of the snake is less than 0.
    Generate
    Store the layout of the buttons to be generated.
    Instructions
    Instruction Screen for the game.
    LeaderBoard
    Leader Board Screen of the game
    LeaderboardStore
    Class to store the highscores of the player
    Magnet
    Type of token to attract all the coins within a certain distance of the snake.
    MainMenu
    Scene having the main menu of the game
    Panel
    Group of different blocks in the game
    Pause
    Pause scene of the game
    Player
    Stores info about the player of this game.
    SceneManager
    Class that acts as an interface between different scenes and is used to switch and communicate between different scenes.
    ScoreInfo
    To serialize the highscore and associate date together
    Shield
    A type of token that is used to move the snake without reducing its length.
    Snake
    The snake for the player.
    SplashS
    Generates the loading screen for the game
    Tokens
    This is an abstract class and cannot be instantiated.
    TopPanel
    The top panel contains the Text field for the current score of the player and the pause button
    Wall
    Represent the wall in the game
